\\\\"The client secret for the OAuth2 client\\\\\\\"}}}]}\\\",\\\"connectorCountry\\\":[\\\"America\\\",\\\"China\\\",\\\"Taiwan\\\",\\\"Britain\\\",\\\"UNITED STATES\\\"],\\\"limitNumber\\\":-1,\\\"shadow\\\":false,\\\"bizType\\\":\\\"ecommerce_marketplaces\\\",\\\"score\\\":5.0,\\\"isHot\\\":true,\\\"available\\\":true,\\\"features\\\":[{\\\"key\\\":\\\"Query Orders\\\",\\\"sort\\\":1},{\\\"key\\\":\\\"Set Inventory\\\",\\\"sort\\\":2},{\\\"key\\\":\\\"Complete Fulfillment\\\",\\\"sort\\\":3},{\\\"key\\\":\\\"Retrieve Order by Name\\\",\\\"sort\\\":4},{\\\"key\\\":\\\"List Fulfillment Orders by ID\\\",\\\"sort\\\":5},{\\\"key\\\":\\\"Cancel Fulfillment\\\",\\\"sort\\\":6},{\\\"key\\\":\\\"List All Fulfillment Services\\\",\\\"sort\\\":7},{\\\"key\\\":\\\"Update Order Note Attributes\\\",\\\"sort\\\":8}],\\\"readme\\\":\\\"## Overview\\\\n\\\\nThe Shopify Admin API is a comprehensive RESTful API that enables developers to programmatically interact with Shopify stores. It provides access to manage various store resources including products, orders, customers, inventory, and more, allowing for seamless integration and automation of e-commerce operations.\\\\n\\\\n## Core Features\\\\n\\\\n### \\\\uD83D\\\\uDECD️ Product Management\\\\n\\\\n- Create, read, update, and delete products\\\\n- Manage product variants, images, and inventory\\\\n- Handle product SEO settings and metadata\\\\n- Control product visibility and availability\\\\n\\\\n### \\\\uD83D\\\\uDCE6 Order Processing\\\\n\\\\n- Access and manage order information\\\\n- Handle order fulfillment and shipping\\\\n- Process refunds and returns\\\\n- Track order status and history\\\\n\\\\n### \\\\uD83D\\\\uDC65 Customer Management\\\\n\\\\n- Manage customer account information\\\\n- Handle customer groups and tags\\\\n- Maintain customer addresses and preferences\\\\n- Track customer order history\\\\n\\\\n### \\\\uD83D\\\\uDCB0 Financial Operations\\\\n\\\\n- Process transactions and payments\\\\n- Manage discount codes and promotions\\\\n- Access financial reporting data\\\\n- Handle pricing and currency settings\\\\n\\\\n### \\\\uD83D\\\\uDD27 Store Configuration\\\\n\\\\n- Manage store settings and preferences\\\\n- Configure shipping and tax settings\\\\n- Handle app installations and themes\\\\n- Control store policies and legal pages\\\\n\\\\n## Supported Resources\\\\n\\\\n| Resource Type | Description                                      |\\\\n| :------------ | :----------------------------------------------- |\\\\n| Products      | Product catalog and variant management           |\\\\n| Orders        | Order processing and lifecycle management        |\\\\n| Customers     | Customer information and relationship management |\\\\n| Inventory     | Stock tracking and warehouse management          |\\\\n| Fulfillments  | Shipping and delivery management                 |\\\\n| Webhooks      | Real-time event notifications                    |\\\\n| Shop          | Store configuration and information              |\\\\n| Collections   | Product grouping and organization                |\\\\n| Discounts     | Promotional pricing and offers                   |\\\\n| Reports       | Analytics and business insights                  |\\\\n\\\\n## Authentication Methods\\\\n\\\\nShopify Admin API supports multiple authentication approaches:\\\\n\\\\n- **Private Apps**: API key and password authentication\\\\n- **Public Apps**: OAuth 2.0 authorization flow\\\\n- **Custom Apps**: Access token-based authentication\\\\n\\\\n## API Capabilities\\\\n\\\\n### Data Operations\\\\n\\\\n- Full CRUD operations on store resources\\\\n- Bulk operations for efficient data management\\\\n- Real-time data synchronization\\\\n- Advanced filtering and search capabilities\\\\n\\\\n### Integration Features\\\\n\\\\n- Webhook notifications for real-time updates\\\\n- Multi-channel inventory management\\\\n- Third-party service integrations\\\\n- Custom app development support\\\\n\\\\n### Business Intelligence\\\\n\\\\n- Comprehensive reporting and analytics\\\\n- Sales performance tracking\\\\n- Customer behavior insights\\\\n- Inventory optimization data\\\\n\\\\n## API Versions\\\\n\\\\n- Current stable version: `2023-10`\\\\n- Versioned API ensures backward compatibility\\\\n- Regular updates with new features and improvements\\\\n- Deprecation notices provided well in advance\\\\n\\\\n## Rate Limits and Quotas\\\\n\\\\n- **REST API**: Bucket-based rate limiting system\\\\n- **GraphQL API**: Query complexity-based quotas\\\\n- Fair usage policies to ensure platform stability\\\\n- Optimized for high-volume operations\\\\n\\\\n## Use Cases\\\\n\\\\n### E-commerce Automation\\\\n\\\\n- Automated inventory management\\\\n- Order processing workflows\\\\n- Customer communication systems\\\\n- Pricing and promotion automation\\\\n\\\\n### Business Intelligence\\\\n\\\\n- Sales analytics and reporting\\\\n- Customer segmentation analysis\\\\n- Product performance tracking\\\\n- Market trend identification\\\\n\\\\n### System Integration\\\\n\\\\n- ERP system synchronization\\\\n- Multi-platform inventory management\\\\n- Third-party marketplace connections\\\\n- Custom business application development\\\\n\\\\n## Key Benefits\\\\n\\\\n- **Scalability**: Handle high-volume operations efficiently\\\\n- **Reliability**: Enterprise-grade API infrastructure\\\\n- **Flexibility**: Comprehensive resource access and control\\\\n- **Security**: Robust authentication and authorization\\\\n- **Documentation**: Extensive developer resources and guides\\\\n\\\\n## Getting Started\\\\n\\\\nTo begin using the Shopify Admin API:\\\\n\\\\n1. Create a Shopify Partner account\\\\n2. Set up your development environment\\\\n3. Choose your authentication method\\\\n4. Review the API documentation\\\\n5. Start building your integration\\\\n\\\\n## Best Practices\\\\n\\\\n- Implement proper error handling\\\\n- Use webhooks for real-time updates\\\\n- Follow API rate limiting guidelines\\\\n- Keep your API credentials secure\\\\n- Stay updated with API version changes\\\\n\\\\n## Resources\\\\n\\\\n- [Official API Documentation](https://shopify.dev/docs/admin-api)\\\\n- [GraphQL Admin API](https://shopify.dev/docs/admin-api/graphql)\\\\n- [Shopify Developer Tools](https://shopify.dev/docs/apps/tools/cli)\\\\n- [API Rate Limits Guide](https://shopify.dev/docs/admin-api/rate-limits)\\\\n- [Webhook Documentation](https://shopify.dev/docs/admin-api/webhooks)\\\\n\\\\n## Support\\\\n\\\\n- Community forums and developer resources\\\\n- Comprehensive documentation and tutorials\\\\n- API changelog and update notifications\\\\n- Developer support channels\\\",\\\"qaData\\\":[{\\\"answer\\\":\\\"xx\\\",\\\"question\\\":\\\"xxx\\\"}]},{\\\"connectorId\\\":50,\\\"sysConfigured\\\":false,\\\"connectorCode\\\":\\\"shopify-shipping\\\",\\\"connectorTags\\\":[{\\\"key\\\":\\\"Order\\\",\\\"sort\\\":2},{\\\"key\\\":\\\"inventory_sync\\\",\\\"sort\\\":3},{\\\"key\\\":\\\"graphql\\\",\\\"sort\\\":4},{\\\"key\\\":\\\"order_mgmt\\\",\\\"sort\\\":5}],\\\"connectorName\\\":\\\"Shopify Shipping App\\\",\\\"connectorDesc\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"connectorTypeCode\\\":\\\"HTTP\\\",\\\"connectorLogoId\\\":33749,\\\"connectorLogoUrl\\\":\\\"https://api-staging.item.com/api/file-app/v1/file/33749/oyJXQdWaSAPO8TUj/view\\\",\\\"connectorConfigValues\\\":\\\"{}\\\",\\\"connectorForm\\\":\\\"{\\\\\\\"Base\\\\\\\": [{\\\\\\\"sort\\\\\\\": 0, \\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"object\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"required\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\"shopDomain\\\\\\\"], \\\\\\\"uiSchema\\\\\\\": {}, \\\\\\\"properties\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\"shopDomain\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\"sort\\\\\\\": 0, \\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"string\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Shop Domain\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"uiSchema\\\\\\\": {}, \\\\\\\"description\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Enter your subdomain (e.g., 'myshop' for 'myshop.myshopify.com')\\\\\\\"}}}], \\\\\\\"Basic\\\\\\\": [{\\\\\\\"sort\\\\\\\": 0, \\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"object\\